main event: Several unidentified flying objects were observed at Edwards Air Force Base, California, on multiple occasions in October 1965.
interesting points: Objects were tracked on radar at speeds between 500-600 knots., The objects exhibited erratic flight patterns, including sharp banking turns., Multiple military personnel reported sightings of bright lights in the sky., At least one object was described as disc-shaped with a metallic appearance., Despite efforts to intercept visually, no aircraft were able to make contact with the objects.
sighted object: Unidentified flying objects emitting bright lights
witness description: Military personnel including airmen and tower operators
